ers DTP funded opportunities for postgraduate research across the breadth of engineering and physical sciences, working on challenges of global significance. We have six strategic research themes: low carbon futures, sustainability, advanced materials and devices, healthy living, data and analysis, and digital media &amp;amp; visual technologies. Our postgraduate research programmes aim to attract cohorts of the very best students from across the world, to embed them in well-resourced and supportive environments in which they can confront the major issues facing our national and global communities, to develop their research abilities through a combination of skills development and training, and student-led research activity, and to graduate them as well-equipped and confident researchers capable of contributing to building the world of tomorrow. Our allocation of funding for the current year 2015/2016 was roughly 25% to Departments in the Faculty of Engineering and Design and 75% to Departments in the Faculty of Science (including Mathematical Sciences). Research in the strategic theme areas is spread across these Departments. Decisions affecting the allocation for 2016/17 will be confirmed by the end of October 2015 to facilitate the recruitment of high quality candidates.
Details of the opportunities for postgraduate research can be found at:
